sequenceDiagram
    participant Browser as Browser (SPA)
    participant IdP as IdP (Entra ID)
    participant Django as Django Backend

    Note over Browser,Django: Pure Django. Frontend uses msal-angular which manages<br/>PKCE, state, and token exchange with Entra ID internally.

    Note over Browser: msal-angular: loginPopup/loginRedirect.<br/>PKCE + state generated internally.<br/>On callback: code exchanged for id_token (PKCE verified by IdP).

    Browser->>IdP: GET /oauth2/v2.0/authorize<br/>?client_id=X&scope=openid+email+profile<br/>&code_challenge=Z&code_challenge_method=S256&state=nonce
    Note over IdP: User authenticates.
    IdP-->>Browser: Auth code callback to SPA redirect URI

    Note over Browser: msal-angular exchanges code for id_token.<br/>Validates id_token internally. Stores in token cache.

    Browser->>Django: POST /api/auth/oidc/token-exchange/<br/>{"id_token": "<Entra id_token>"}
    Note over Django: Custom auth backend:<br/>1. Verify id_token signature (Entra JWKS).<br/>2. Validate iss, aud, exp.<br/>3. Extract email from trusted claims.<br/>4. Get or create auth_user by email.<br/>5. Issue DRF Token.
    Django-->>Browser: 200 {"token": "DRF_TOKEN", "django_id": "42"}

    Note over Browser: Store DRF token for subsequent API calls.
